Graticule Asset Management Asia (“GAMA”) is a global alternative asset manager founded by Adam Levinson. GAMA manages alternative investment strategies that pursue superior risk-adjusted returns surrounding distinctive, Asia–related macroeconomic themes. Headquartered in Singapore, GAMA has ofﬁces in New York, San Francisco and London.
GAMA operates through regulated affiliates that are registered in the U.S. with the Securities and Exchange Commission. Its U.S. affiliate is registered with the CFTC, its Singapore affiliate is licensed by the Monetary Authority of Singapore and its U.K. affiliate is authorized and regulated by the Financial Conduct Authority.


























